WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.771 --> 00:00:02.597
<v ->For anyone who has been through the process</v>

2
00:00:02.597 --> 00:00:05.052
of the passing of a loved one, you know that

3
00:00:05.052 --> 00:00:07.982
there are moments that are painful and trying to one's soul.

4
00:00:07.982 --> 00:00:10.955
This is especially true when it's a person's spouse

5
00:00:10.955 --> 00:00:13.536
and age has taken its toll through dementia

6
00:00:13.536 --> 00:00:16.388
and a slow or even rapid decline of health.

7
00:00:16.388 --> 00:00:19.503
Fern Stewart Welsh has walked this walk and is sharing

8
00:00:19.503 --> 00:00:22.982
her experience in her book, The Heart Knows the Way.

9
00:00:22.982 --> 00:00:25.582
This beautiful and charming woman had to dig

10
00:00:25.582 --> 00:00:27.887
down into the deepest part of her being

11
00:00:27.887 --> 00:00:30.989
to connect to the sublime part that knows all

12
00:00:30.989 --> 00:00:34.217
to learn about what her beloved husband was experiencing

13
00:00:34.217 --> 00:00:36.745
as his mind and body slipped away.

14
00:00:36.745 --> 00:00:39.017
What she learned will benefit each and every one

15
00:00:39.017 --> 00:00:41.655
of us that faces a loved one's decline.

16
00:00:41.655 --> 00:00:46.391 line:15% 
(soothing music playing)

17
00:00:50.301 --> 00:00:54.206
<v Voiceover>This is such a sweet and confirming</v>

18
00:00:54.206 --> 00:00:56.606
and important work that you've done.

19
00:00:56.606 --> 00:01:00.488
And just to lay a little bit of foundation here,

20
00:01:00.488 --> 00:01:03.133
certainly someone noted very well in this field,

21
00:01:03.133 --> 00:01:05.577
Elizabeth Kubler-Ross, and you were very close friends.

22
00:01:05.577 --> 00:01:09.426
And she actually helped you through the death and dying

23
00:01:09.426 --> 00:01:12.454
and experience of your sweetie pie, Ken.

24
00:01:12.454 --> 00:01:13.338
<v ->Yes.</v>

25
00:01:13.338 --> 00:01:16.492
<v Voiceover>And so, and you are, now at this time,</v>

26
00:01:16.492 --> 00:01:18.762
carrying a lot of this work forward.

27
00:01:18.762 --> 00:01:22.849
And really, this book is sort of your flagship effort

28
00:01:22.849 --> 00:01:26.593
in helping people understand the process

29
00:01:26.593 --> 00:01:29.044
we all are going to go through at one time or another,

30
00:01:30.054 --> 00:01:33.749
short or long, in the process of death and dying.

31
00:01:33.749 --> 00:01:35.221
Can you give a little bit of background

32
00:01:35.221 --> 00:01:38.006
about your relationship with Ken

33
00:01:38.006 --> 00:01:40.945
and where the beginning

34
00:01:40.945 --> 00:01:43.474
of the end actually began?

35
00:01:43.474 --> 00:01:44.992
<v ->Well, it makes me smile because one</v>

36
00:01:44.992 --> 00:01:47.125
of the greatest things that I've experienced

37
00:01:47.125 --> 00:01:49.290
as a result of going through what I did

38
00:01:49.290 --> 00:01:51.562
is that whenever I think of my late husband,

39
00:01:51.562 --> 00:01:54.187
I don't think of it in a sad way.

40
00:01:54.187 --> 00:01:57.364
It makes me smile within, all right.

41
00:01:57.364 --> 00:01:59.753
And I guess the experience started

42
00:01:59.753 --> 00:02:02.712
about 15 years before his death in 2002.

43
00:02:03.891 --> 00:02:06.463
He started having certain illnesses,

44
00:02:06.463 --> 00:02:09.247
and it was quite awhile before I realized

45
00:02:09.247 --> 00:02:11.145
that he was not going to be able to come back

46
00:02:11.145 --> 00:02:14.879
from those illnesses, but was indeed in that process

47
00:02:14.879 --> 00:02:18.010
of the decline that would end in death.

48
00:02:18.010 --> 00:02:20.717
<v ->And I guess that was probably within five, six, seven</v>

49
00:02:20.717 --> 00:02:23.996
years after he began having illnesses at different times.

50
00:02:23.996 --> 00:02:26.322
<v Voiceover>So this was a long, kind of,</v>

51
00:02:26.322 --> 00:02:29.436
in one sense, third-dimensionally downhill slide

52
00:02:29.436 --> 00:02:33.264
on a physical level, and you might even say,

53
00:02:33.264 --> 00:02:35.398
emotional or mental on some levels

54
00:02:35.398 --> 00:02:37.531
from what you understood in the beginning.

55
00:02:37.531 --> 00:02:41.275
But you began, as it was becoming more challenging

56
00:02:41.275 --> 00:02:43.344
as his health was slipping away,

57
00:02:43.344 --> 00:02:46.795
you began really looking inside for answers

58
00:02:46.795 --> 00:02:48.695
and that seems like that's kind of

59
00:02:48.695 --> 00:02:50.335
where this really journey begins.

60
00:02:50.335 --> 00:02:51.509
Can you talk about that?

61
00:02:51.509 --> 00:02:55.118
<v ->Yes, it's called sheer desperation, absolute desperation.</v>

62
00:02:56.008 --> 00:02:58.423
I wanted to approach this with my husband,

63
00:02:58.423 --> 00:03:00.396
who I loved dearly.

64
00:03:00.396 --> 00:03:03.041
I wanted to approach this in a way that was more helpful,

65
00:03:03.041 --> 00:03:07.916
more enlightening, and more loving, and I tried.

66
00:03:08.956 --> 00:03:11.915
For about four or five years, I was totally unsuccessful

67
00:03:11.915 --> 00:03:14.958
and what I was doing was using just my sheer energy

68
00:03:14.958 --> 00:03:18.124
and force of will, and I was becoming exhausted.

69
00:03:19.104 --> 00:03:21.272
I didn't recuperate from even a light cold

70
00:03:21.272 --> 00:03:23.447
or something like that very easily.

71
00:03:23.447 --> 00:03:26.721
So I did what I guess what millions of people do

72
00:03:26.721 --> 00:03:28.652
when they come to a point like this.

73
00:03:28.652 --> 00:03:31.574
I went within, and I was determined

74
00:03:31.574 --> 00:03:34.924
that I would either have that connection with the

75
00:03:34.924 --> 00:03:38.145
eternal and sublime something that's within everyone,

76
00:03:38.145 --> 00:03:41.538
or I would know the reason why not.

77
00:03:41.538 --> 00:03:44.118
And so I devoted my life to that.

78
00:03:44.118 --> 00:03:46.544
<v Voiceover>How did you go about doing this?</v>

79
00:03:46.544 --> 00:03:49.269
How did that process work for you?

80
00:03:49.269 --> 00:03:52.138
<v ->Well, I had been a journaler all my life,</v>

81
00:03:52.138 --> 00:03:55.998
well most of my life, anyway about 40 years, daily.

82
00:03:55.998 --> 00:03:59.475
That had continued during this time with my husband,

83
00:03:59.475 --> 00:04:01.802
and I used that, I would write out

84
00:04:01.802 --> 00:04:04.424
all my cares and my concerns and pray.

85
00:04:04.424 --> 00:04:07.186
And then I did what I have done most of my life.

86
00:04:07.186 --> 00:04:08.998
When nothing happened, no burning bush,

87
00:04:08.998 --> 00:04:10.737
no immediate, whatever,

88
00:04:10.737 --> 00:04:13.693
I went out and tried to do it myself.

89
00:04:13.693 --> 00:04:15.965
And this time, I was determined

90
00:04:15.965 --> 00:04:17.778
that that wasn't going to be the case,

91
00:04:17.778 --> 00:04:21.074
and so day by day, I went within, I prayed,

92
00:04:22.104 --> 00:04:23.976
and the process was such that the more

93
00:04:23.976 --> 00:04:27.879
that I went within, the more content I became

94
00:04:27.879 --> 00:04:30.416
at being in meditation and in prayer

95
00:04:31.416 --> 00:04:33.735
and being within myself because prior to this,

96
00:04:33.735 --> 00:04:35.921
I had been working, I retired.

97
00:04:35.921 --> 00:04:38.491
And when I did retire, I had time.

98
00:04:38.491 --> 00:04:40.795
and didn't have to look at the clock

99
00:04:40.795 --> 00:04:43.654
and be concerned about how much time I spent.

100
00:04:43.654 --> 00:04:46.246
So sometimes, I would spend an hour or two.

101
00:04:46.246 --> 00:04:48.571
I would say prayers for me, for my family,

102
00:04:48.571 --> 00:04:52.123
for the world, for the Earth, and I would cry,

103
00:04:52.123 --> 00:04:56.509
and I would do all sorts of beseeching type things,

104
00:04:57.539 --> 00:05:01.253
and just continued day after day after day.

105
00:05:02.293 --> 00:05:03.781
The more desperate the situation got,

106
00:05:03.781 --> 00:05:07.383
when I could see that Ken was losing awareness of his life.

107
00:05:08.417 --> 00:05:11.285
And everything around him, then I really spent

108
00:05:11.285 --> 00:05:14.793
the time there, and my daughter suggested a book to me

109
00:05:14.793 --> 00:05:18.133
called Secrets of the Vine and I read it.

110
00:05:18.133 --> 00:05:19.650
And what I discovered was that

111
00:05:20.650 --> 00:05:23.539
it's certainly a different process than what I was doing.

112
00:05:23.539 --> 00:05:26.753
Instead of crying and begging and pleading, it indicated

113
00:05:26.753 --> 00:05:29.986
that I was to spend that time as I would

114
00:05:29.986 --> 00:05:33.348
with a very dear friend, getting to know that dear friend,

115
00:05:34.418 --> 00:05:37.561
you know, sharing all of my concerns, my desires

116
00:05:37.561 --> 00:05:39.374
with my loves, my everything.

117
00:05:39.374 --> 00:05:42.019
And literally, that's what I focused on.

118
00:05:42.019 --> 00:05:44.711
And then one day, I wrote out, you know,

119
00:05:44.711 --> 00:05:47.981
I want a personal relationship with you God.

120
00:05:47.981 --> 00:05:49.657
I don't know how to do it.

121
00:05:49.657 --> 00:05:51.650
How does a little person like myself

122
00:05:51.650 --> 00:05:54.392
have a personal relationship with the God

123
00:05:54.392 --> 00:05:56.578
of the universe, the allness of the universe?

124
00:05:56.578 --> 00:05:59.476
And innocently, within my brain

125
00:05:59.476 --> 00:06:02.274
and I think my heart too, came that message.

126
00:06:02.274 --> 00:06:04.743
Fern, Fern, Fern, I'm going to cry.

127
00:06:04.743 --> 00:06:06.594
You have always had it.

128
00:06:06.594 --> 00:06:09.232
<v Voiceover>Right, it's always been there.</v>

129
00:06:09.232 --> 00:06:10.448
<v ->It's always been there.</v>

130
00:06:10.448 --> 00:06:12.325
<v Voiceover>Now while this was happening,</v>

131
00:06:12.325 --> 00:06:14.968
Ken was going through some pretty dramatic stuff.

132
00:06:16.198 --> 00:06:18.978
He had, at one point, finally had to go

133
00:06:18.978 --> 00:06:22.584
into a facility where he had assisted living

134
00:06:22.584 --> 00:06:24.770
because his problems were becoming

135
00:06:24.770 --> 00:06:27.415
too challenging for you to deal with.

136
00:06:27.415 --> 00:06:28.370
<v ->Right.</v>

137
00:06:28.370 --> 00:06:30.039
<v Voiceover>In addition, there were a lot</v>

138
00:06:30.039 --> 00:06:32.215
of emotional challenges, and some of them

139
00:06:32.215 --> 00:06:35.079
were almost comical in reading your book.

140
00:06:35.079 --> 00:06:36.918
It's not funny when you're that person.

141
00:06:36.918 --> 00:06:37.811
<v ->No.</v>

142
00:06:37.811 --> 00:06:39.729
<v Voiceover>To see your husband, you know,</v>

143
00:06:39.729 --> 00:06:41.937
asking you to make wedding arrangements

144
00:06:41.937 --> 00:06:44.788
with the 21 year-old nurse (laughs).

145
00:06:44.788 --> 00:06:45.756
<v ->Right.</v>

146
00:06:45.756 --> 00:06:47.783
<v Voiceover>Because he knows you know him well.</v>

147
00:06:47.783 --> 00:06:50.847
And these moments that one would say are not

148
00:06:50.847 --> 00:06:53.843
particularly lucid, but that are there all the time.

149
00:06:54.883 --> 00:06:58.818
And so, what was happening on an emotional level

150
00:06:58.818 --> 00:07:02.786
in you as you were dealing with these bizarre sorts

151
00:07:02.786 --> 00:07:05.975
of encounters with your husband on a regular basis?

152
00:07:05.975 --> 00:07:07.802
<v ->First of all, it was devastating</v>

153
00:07:07.802 --> 00:07:11.254
because I could not believe that this man who adored me

154
00:07:11.254 --> 00:07:14.753
and who I adored would be going

155
00:07:14.753 --> 00:07:17.441
through this kind of experience.

156
00:07:17.441 --> 00:07:20.450
That sent me running back to communion with God

157
00:07:20.450 --> 00:07:22.423
with that eternal and sublime something

158
00:07:22.423 --> 00:07:24.929
that's within you, me, and everyone.

159
00:07:24.929 --> 00:07:27.936
And that's when I was told, if he finds solace

160
00:07:29.326 --> 00:07:32.373
in any relationship or imagined relationship,

161
00:07:32.373 --> 00:07:35.115
because every soul likes that companionship,

162
00:07:35.115 --> 00:07:37.461
that feeling of human companionship,

163
00:07:37.461 --> 00:07:39.776
you must allow it and it will not harm you

164
00:07:39.776 --> 00:07:41.749
in any way, shape, or form.

165
00:07:41.749 --> 00:07:44.287
<v Voiceover>So initially, the ego might hear this.</v>

166
00:07:44.287 --> 00:07:45.909
What happens there?

167
00:07:47.729 --> 00:07:49.675
<v ->The ego was devastated.</v>

168
00:07:49.675 --> 00:07:52.895
I could not believe that this was going on,

169
00:07:52.895 --> 00:07:56.031
that he could forget me, and could forget

170
00:07:56.031 --> 00:07:59.937
our relationship, and I did have a real problem with that.

171
00:07:59.937 --> 00:08:02.305
It took me quite awhile to be able to deal with that.

172
00:08:02.305 --> 00:08:05.163
And that went on off-and-on for almost a year.

173
00:08:05.163 --> 00:08:08.598
<v Voiceover>Right, and so, ultimately,</v>

