even though he may not react to me as he would normally,

255
00:11:34.652 --> 00:11:37.290
he did seem to know my energy, at least.

256
00:11:37.290 --> 00:11:40.232
So I could tell when he was there and when he was here,

257
00:11:40.232 --> 00:11:42.056
when he was lucid in front of me.

258
00:11:42.056 --> 00:11:45.224
And he became very facile near the end

259
00:11:45.224 --> 00:11:48.167
of his life with being able to go back and forth.

260
00:11:48.167 --> 00:11:50.439
And it was really fascinating because he had been

261
00:11:50.439 --> 00:11:54.492
the type of man who was very fun-loving (laughs),

262
00:11:55.522 --> 00:11:58.108
and he teased a lot, and so instead of saying,

263
00:11:58.108 --> 00:12:00.732
"Oh, you look wonderful today," he would say,

264
00:12:00.732 --> 00:12:03.253
"For a fat girl, you clean up pretty good."

265
00:12:03.253 --> 00:12:04.528
You know, things like that.

266
00:12:04.528 --> 00:12:06.652
So one day I'm with him and in this interchange,

267
00:12:06.652 --> 00:12:09.436
he comes back and I can tell that he's there

268
00:12:09.436 --> 00:12:12.647
with me totally, and he says, "When I feel the love

269
00:12:12.647 --> 00:12:15.632
"coming from you, it makes me want to return it."

270
00:12:16.582 --> 00:12:18.864
And that was absolutely incredible

271
00:12:18.864 --> 00:12:21.742
because he had not been that kind of man

272
00:12:21.742 --> 00:12:24.356
who would express his emotions in that way.

273
00:12:25.523 --> 00:12:29.147
So I think that as I was being fine-tuned,

274
00:12:29.147 --> 00:12:31.526
is about the best way I can express it.

275
00:12:31.526 --> 00:12:34.463
As I was being fine-tuned in this energy,

276
00:12:34.463 --> 00:12:35.887
I was able to bring more of it out

277
00:12:37.057 --> 00:12:39.876
to my associations and interactions with Ken.

278
00:12:41.046 --> 00:12:44.590
I became able to accept what was going on,

279
00:12:45.720 --> 00:12:48.280
and try to stay out of the way with my ego

280
00:12:48.280 --> 00:12:50.392
and stay out of the way with what my desires were

281
00:12:50.392 --> 00:12:54.200
and just help this soul make his journey

282
00:12:54.200 --> 00:12:57.613
in his soul's time and make his transition.

283
00:12:58.583 --> 00:13:01.144
<v Voiceover>What also was interesting was that,</v>

284
00:13:01.144 --> 00:13:04.375
because he was going between dimensions

285
00:13:04.375 --> 00:13:08.364
and going to the other side, he was able

286
00:13:08.364 --> 00:13:12.215
to dip into sources of love and understanding

287
00:13:12.215 --> 00:13:14.637
in such that, he may not have had access to

288
00:13:14.637 --> 00:13:17.576
within himself in his third dimesional life.

289
00:13:17.576 --> 00:13:18.422
<v ->Right.</v>

290
00:13:18.422 --> 00:13:20.160
<v Voiceover>Is it a two-way street then,</v>

291
00:13:20.160 --> 00:13:21.686
bringing the love both ways?

292
00:13:21.686 --> 00:13:24.086
You committed to giving it, and he was

293
00:13:24.086 --> 00:13:26.038
already experiencing some over there.

294
00:13:26.038 --> 00:13:29.071
How did this work between you then,

295
00:13:29.071 --> 00:13:32.182
on a soul-level from what your guidance was telling you

296
00:13:32.182 --> 00:13:34.516
about the flowing of love back-and-forth

297
00:13:34.516 --> 00:13:36.385
from his comings and goings?

298
00:13:36.385 --> 00:13:39.040
<v ->I can remember that as he became more facile</v>

299
00:13:40.250 --> 00:13:44.101
as he became more facile on these journeys,

300
00:13:44.101 --> 00:13:47.114
and that he was mirroring me, my love.

301
00:13:47.114 --> 00:13:48.686
We mirroed each other.

302
00:13:48.686 --> 00:13:51.990
That's about the best way I can answer that.

303
00:13:53.640 --> 00:13:56.256
And I don't know, I had no indication

304
00:13:56.256 --> 00:14:00.110
that he had, from verbally, that he had a new understanding.

305
00:14:00.110 --> 00:14:03.242
What he brought back was love

306
00:14:03.242 --> 00:14:07.000
and it was indicative in that one thing that he said

307
00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:08.238
and a couple of others, and I don't remember

308
00:14:08.238 --> 00:14:10.059
the others right now.

309
00:14:10.059 --> 00:14:12.739
But mainly, from the way,

310
00:14:12.739 --> 00:14:14.925
he became soft, he became,

311
00:14:14.925 --> 00:14:17.122
he had been a very powerful businessman,

312
00:14:17.122 --> 00:14:19.446
and a very in-control businessman,

313
00:14:19.446 --> 00:14:22.103
and yet he became very soft.

314
00:14:22.103 --> 00:14:23.469
I mean he was always tender and loving

315
00:14:23.469 --> 00:14:27.320
to me and to family, but he also had a very strong side

316
00:14:27.320 --> 00:14:30.250
in order to operate in the corporate world.

317
00:14:31.260 --> 00:14:33.612
So he became very soft and very tender,

318
00:14:33.612 --> 00:14:35.468
and very child-like.

319
00:14:36.492 --> 00:14:39.414
And those are the major things that I noticed.

320
00:14:40.364 --> 00:14:42.762
<v Voiceover>Back to his more essential nature.</v>

321
00:14:42.762 --> 00:14:44.007
<v ->Right.</v>

322
00:14:44.007 --> 00:14:46.351
<v Voiceover>So when the time started drawing near</v>

323
00:14:47.371 --> 00:14:50.326
toward the very last couple of days of his life,

324
00:14:50.326 --> 00:14:52.118
what kind of information was flowing

325
00:14:52.118 --> 00:14:54.027
through, at that time, for you?

326
00:14:54.027 --> 00:14:57.440
<v ->Persevere, persevere, persevere.</v>

327
00:14:57.440 --> 00:15:00.516
You will be victorious, everything that you have experienced

328
00:15:00.516 --> 00:15:03.168
in your life has brought you to this point.

329
00:15:05.802 --> 00:15:07.466
<v Voiceover>Can you expand on that a little bit</v>

330
00:15:07.466 --> 00:15:10.644
to this point, why this point for each one

331
00:15:10.644 --> 00:15:14.670
of us to deal with this situation?

332
00:15:16.522 --> 00:15:19.209
<v ->Maybe I'm thinking about, now that you ask a question,</v>

333
00:15:19.209 --> 00:15:21.950
I'm thinking about the fact that when this all started,

334
00:15:21.950 --> 00:15:25.437
I thought, "Will I be enough?

335
00:15:26.437 --> 00:15:27.918
"Will I be able to do this in a way

336
00:15:27.918 --> 00:15:29.475
"that my heart and soul desires?

337
00:15:29.475 --> 00:15:31.283
"Will I be able to do it in a helpful,

338
00:15:31.283 --> 00:15:34.078
"life-affirming, spiritually-affirming way?"

339
00:15:35.278 --> 00:15:38.281
And I guess that was my concern all the way through.

340
00:15:38.281 --> 00:15:41.320
And I think what was meant by that guidance was

341
00:15:41.320 --> 00:15:44.914
that, at this point, I was ready to take it all the way

342
00:15:44.914 --> 00:15:46.493
and should have no fear about that.

343
00:15:47.683 --> 00:15:48.952
<v Voiceover>And there really are just some</v>

344
00:15:48.952 --> 00:15:50.916
beautiful pearls of wisdom in there for each

345
00:15:50.916 --> 00:15:53.904
of these little, daily situations that were painful

346
00:15:53.904 --> 00:15:56.132
that you encountered to help you through there.

347
00:15:56.132 --> 00:15:57.910
I mean, I highly recommend anybody

348
00:15:57.910 --> 00:16:02.873
that's going into this kind of stage with somebody.

349
00:16:02.873 --> 00:16:05.956
It's a wonderful, gentle kind of guidebook for them

350
00:16:05.956 --> 00:16:08.558
to help them understand from the other perspective

351
00:16:08.558 --> 00:16:11.654
and not just their own fears, and as you say, pains,

352
00:16:11.654 --> 00:16:15.312
and you know, little whiplashes of the ego and so forth.

353
00:16:16.262 --> 00:16:18.213
<v ->I think one of the things I would like to stress is</v>

354
00:16:18.213 --> 00:16:21.462
that it's possible, number one,

355
00:16:21.462 --> 00:16:24.299
for a person, an ordinary person

356
00:16:24.299 --> 00:16:28.085
to accompany a loved one in a way that is life-affirming

357
00:16:28.085 --> 00:16:31.279
and is helpful and is loving, and I think

358
00:16:31.279 --> 00:16:35.652
that's very important, and I can say that because I did it.

359
00:16:35.652 --> 00:16:38.625
And I know that if I did it, anybody else can.

360
00:16:38.625 --> 00:16:40.183
<v Voiceover>And what effect did it have</v>

361
00:16:40.183 --> 00:16:43.822
after Ken made his transition and you were going

362
00:16:43.822 --> 00:16:46.959
through the normal process people go through?

363
00:16:46.959 --> 00:16:49.347
What was different in what you experienced

364
00:16:49.347 --> 00:16:51.161
versus maybe somebody who hadn't been able

365
00:16:51.161 --> 00:16:54.318
to go through it with that kind of knowledge and grace?

366
00:16:55.288 --> 00:16:57.359
<v ->Immediately, I don't think there was any difference.</v>

367
00:16:58.760 --> 00:17:00.931
I did 60 days of mourning

368
00:17:00.931 --> 00:17:03.869
and I gave myself to the process totally.

369
00:17:03.869 --> 00:17:07.736
I lived, ate, slept, thought, you know, cried,

370
00:17:07.736 --> 00:17:09.557
did all the things that any human

371
00:17:09.557 --> 00:17:12.546
being would do that loves someone.

372
00:17:12.546 --> 00:17:16.015
After the 60 days, Mrs. Kubler-Ross called me,

373
00:17:16.015 --> 00:17:19.056
and said, "Fern, have you finished your book?"

374
00:17:19.056 --> 00:17:22.233
And I said, "No," I'm crying.

375
00:17:22.233 --> 00:17:23.833
And she said, "You must finish it,"

376
00:17:23.833 --> 00:17:25.295
because she had read the book,

377
00:17:25.295 --> 00:17:28.036
the manuscript before it was complete.

378
00:17:28.036 --> 00:17:30.425
And so she encouraged me to continue it.

379
00:17:31.413 --> 00:17:33.561
And that caused me to go to the computer,

380
00:17:33.561 --> 00:17:36.515
and to look at the book that I had been writing

381
00:17:36.515 --> 00:17:39.086
to chronicle my husband's death and dying,

382
00:17:39.086 --> 00:17:42.182
and that seemed to be

383
00:17:44.616 --> 00:17:47.630
a positive step in me working through it

384
00:17:47.630 --> 00:17:50.310
because writing to me is a catharsis.

385
00:17:50.310 --> 00:17:52.162
It's a natural healing process.

386
00:17:52.162 --> 00:17:54.625
I've done that all my life, so I think

387
00:17:54.625 --> 00:17:56.428
that started me on the next stage,

388
00:17:56.428 --> 00:18:00.891
which is finishing that book and I have not looked back.

389
00:18:00.891 --> 00:18:04.214
I found myself soon filled with joy

390
00:18:04.214 --> 00:18:06.486
with boundless enthusiasm for life,

391
00:18:07.446 --> 00:18:10.102
knowing that there is a way to go through that.

392
00:18:10.102 --> 00:18:12.050
That is diametrically opposed to

393
00:18:12.050 --> 00:18:14.367
what many people experience.

394
00:18:14.367 --> 00:18:16.683
Death isn't the most horrible thing in the world.

395
00:18:16.683 --> 00:18:20.336
It's meant to be a sacred, life-affirming,

396
00:18:20.336 --> 00:18:21.719
spiritually-enlightening event,

397
00:18:21.719 --> 00:18:23.196
and that's what I experienced,

398
00:18:23.196 --> 00:18:25.585
that's what I'm going to take out to the world.

399
